<%# 
  arma-config.ejs — NOT USED IN CURRENT POC

  The Arma orderer requires per-node config files generated
  by the armageddon CLI tool. These cannot be templated simply
  because armageddon embeds cryptographic material and party
  topology into each node's config during generation.

  Current approach: pre-generated placeholder configs in arma-configs/
  are copied into fablo-target-fabricx/arma-configs/ by generate.ts.

  Full implementation would:
  1. Run armageddon generate --config=input.yaml --output=arma-configs/
  2. Template the input.yaml using EJS from fabric-x-config.json
  3. Mount generated configs into orderer containers

  This file is kept as a placeholder for that future implementation.
%>